						<b>Songpyun (pine flavored half-moon-shaped rice cake)</b><br><br>
						Rice flour is kneaded with hot water and stuffed with beans, chestnuts, or sesame seeds to make half moon-shaped or clam-shaped dumplings. Then, it is steamed on a layer of pine needles. It is a representative food of Chu-seok holiday (Korean Thanksgiving day).</td>
